description: Out of Thin Air: Murder in Iceland Sociopolitical Documentary hosted by Dylan Howitt, published by BBC broadcasted as part of BBC Storyville series in 2017 - English narration. http://docuwiki.net/images/a/ad/Out-of-Thin-Air-Murder-in-Iceland-Cover.jpg Information ------------------------------ In 1974 two men vanished several months apart. Iceland, with a population of just over 200,000, was a close, tight-knit community where everyone knew everyone, but the police got nowhere: there were no bodies, no witnesses and no forensic evidence. Then six suspects were arrested and confessed to the murders, many facing long, harsh sentences. It seemed like justice had been done, but nothing could be further from the truth.
